Billionaire business mogul, Femi Otedola has reacted excitedly to his daughter, Temi Otedola’s engagement to her singer boo, Mr Eazi. On Sunday, Temi via her Twitter handles shared a video where the “Banku” music pioneer was seen in the cool of the evening, by the seashore on one knee proposing marriage to her with a ring held out. After accepting the proposal, Mr Eazi slipped the ring onto the actress’ finger, stood up and they each hug sealing, the proposal with a passionate kiss.   I won’t reveal my new man until we’re married…     Tekno to Davido: don’t talk to me again if…     Find my man, DJ Cuppy tells Mr Eazi, sister   Temi made sure to caption the video with an infinity sign to show their union will be forever. Reacting to his 26-year-old daughter’s engagement, Otedola in a post which he accompanied with a happy emoji, wrote: “Somebody is taking my baby.”